text: Helen Mary Warnock, Baroness Warnock, (née Wilson; 14 April 1924 – 20 March 2019) was an English philosopher. She was best known for chairing an inquiry whose report formed the basis of the Human Fertilisation and Embryology Act 1990. She was Mistress of Girton College, Cambridge from 1984 to 1991. Warnock died, aged 94, on 20 March 2019. ==References== Category:1924 births Category:2019 deaths Category:English philosophers Category:Academics of the University of Cambridge Category:Writers from Hampshire
